A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Education – High School Diploma – Veterans of Armed Conflicts
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing certain individuals honorably discharged from military
4 service to obtain a high school diploma if the individual withdrew from a certain
5 public or private school to enlist in the armed forces during a certain armed conflict;
6 and generally relating to high school diplomas for veterans.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
8 Article – Education
9 Section 7–206.1
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Education
15 7–206.1.
16 (a) An individual honorably discharged from military service may apply to obtain
17 a high school diploma if the individual withdrew from a regular full–time public or private
18 high school accredited by the State Board to enlist in the armed forces of the United States
19 during[:
20 (1) World War II;
21 (2) The Korean Conflict; or
